article.headline: (24) BOSTON COLLEGE 73, BROWN 45
article.story:
PROVIDENCE, Rhode Island (Ticker) -- Amber Jackson scored 19 
points to lead No. 25 past Brown, 73-45, in the 2003 Brown
Classic.

Jackson, who was named the tournament MVP, connected on 8-of-15
shooting and distributed seven assists for the Eagles (7-0), who
outscored the Bears, 43-15, in the second half.

Jessalyn Deveny delivered 16 points, six rebounds and five
assists for Boston College, which outrebounded Brown, 40-28.

Lisa Macchia finished with nine boards and 15 points, and Clare
Droesh provided 13 points off the bench for the Eagles, who
received 21 points in all from their reserves.

Tanara Golston scored 18 points for the Bears (2-5), who were
held to just 33 percent shooting.

Nyama Mitchell had 13 points and four rebounds for Brown, which
failed to score over the final 7:17.
